---
import "../styles/global.css";
import "../styles/index.css";
import ProgressBar from "./progressbar.astro";
---

<html>
  <head>
    <link
      rel="icon"
      type="image/png"
      href="/DiET_teaching_blog_hdfs//favicon-h.png"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <ProgressBar step={1} total={5} />
    <h1 style="text-align: center;">HDFS</h1>

    <p class="py-8">
      HDFS stands for Hadoop distributed file systems and is a data center that
      is used to store large amount data and files that are too big to store on
      a single machine. These files are typically in the GB to TB range. HDFS's
      architecture is centralized and consists of a Master Node, named the
      NameNode, and thousands of DataNodes. The NameNode keeps track how files
      are split up and where the pieces are stored. The DataNodes store the
      individual data blocks. Multiple DataNodes are stacked on top of each
      other in a rack, and the racks form the data center. Click Next to see how
      files are split up.
    </p>

    <img
      src="../public/architecture.png"
      class="center"
      alt="The architecture of HDFS"
    />

    <!-- References to previous and next page -->
    <div class="flex justify-center gap-4 mt-6">
      <a
        href=".."
        class="px-4 py-2 bg-[oklch(0.3816_0.1558_356.93)] text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-[oklch(0.6831_0.1558_356.93)]"
      >
        Back Home
      </a>

      <a
        href="../lesson2/"
        class="px-4 py-2 bg-[oklch(0.3816_0.1558_356.93)] text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-[oklch(0.6831_0.1558_356.93)] ml-2"
      >
        Next
      </a>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
